Yobe State Governor, Hon. Mai Mala Buni, has commiserated with his Deputy, Idi Barde Gubana, over the death of his elder brother, Alh. Muhammadu Barde Gubana. Buni on Wednesday, through his Spokesperson Mamman Mohammed, described the passing of Alh. Muhammadu as a painful loss to the family, Gubana community and the state. Gov. Buni said, “It is with great pain and sadness that we received the news of the death of elder Muhammadu, who died yesterday. “Late Muhammadu died at a time when his wise counselling is much needed, but that is the wish of Allah SWT our creator.” The governor prayed to Almighty Allah to forgive the shortcomings of the deceased, grant him Aljannatur Firdaus and to the family, the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.